" git log --oneline origin/main..main"      //origin/main is a branch!


Note: git push origin main      //push main branch
      git push origin           //if the current branch is main
      git push                  //origin is default!

Note: sometime we have error on pushing,
      that's because some new commit exist on server
      we need to pull first (so merge or rebased happened)
      then pushing.
      never make a force push, it will drop other developer commits!

Note: push occurred on current branch,
      so we need switch or use another branch name on command to push it.
      so until now we just pushed the "main" branch on git hub
      I used "all" option to push all the branches!
      "git push --all"
